  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT361-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">varaivu malintavaḻit tōḻi “naṉkāṟṟiṉāy” eṉṟāṭkuk kiḻatti colliyatu. </p>


        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered by HER to the one, who said “you have well had
          the strength”, [namely] the confidante, when she rejoiced over the [coming] marriage. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT361">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> amma vāḻi tōḻi yaṉṉaik</l>
          <l> kuyarnilai yulakamuñ ciṟitā lavarmalai</l>
          <l> mālaip peyta maṇaṅkama ḻuntiyoṭu</l>
          <l> kālai vanta kāntaṇ muḻumutaṉ</l>
          <l> mellilai kuḻaiya muyaṅkalu</l>
          <l> milluyttu naṭutaluṅ kaṭiyā tōḷē.</l>


        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>Alas, oh friend, for mother</l>
          <l>indeed also the upper world would be a small [return],</l>
          <l>she who did not prevent [me from] setting up in the house</l>
          <l rend="indent">and embracing, softly , the tender leaves</l>
          <l rend="indent">of the whole stem of the Malabar lily, come in the morning</l>
          <l rend="indent2">with the river, fragrant with the scent rained in the evening</l>
          <l rend="indent6">from his mountain.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
